                <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan> Arminio <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/>Caecin<supplied reason="lost">a</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="3"/>Caecinia Ar<supplied reason="lost">mini</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="4"/>Paetus <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Bacci: Caecina Paetus möglicherweise identisch mit Ehemann jener Arria, die unter Claudius Selbstmord beging (Pin., Ep. 3,16). Ergänzungsvorschlag Torelli: C. Arminio [- f. Gallo] / Caecin[ae Paeto] / Caecinia Ar[mini Galli f.?] / Paetus [et Gallus? fil. fec.?].</p>
            </div>
